fields.title: Guide for RU 630
fields.text:
1. Download and install Win32DiskImager-0.9.5’ program.
  2. Download service image for SDSN (SD card serial number) detection.
  3. Burn the image to the known good micro SD card with ‘Win32DiskImager-0.9.5’ program.
  4. Insert microSD card with the burned image into the device card reader and turn on the device by pressing ‘power on button’ for 1 sec.
  5. SDSN should appear on the display (device should turn off by itself in a few seconds; SDSN should be on the display).
  6. Open Jenkins builder using direct link https://tickets.obreey-products.com/jenkins/ and log in.
  7. Select ‘626-sdcard’ in the appeared list of projects.
  8. Select display type, for XH7 put WF and VCOM level to the empty fields of Jenkins builder. 
  10. Put SDSN and device serial number into the empty fields of Jenkins builder, select your e-mail from the drop-down list and press ’Build’ button.
  11. Open selected in previous point e-mail box and download image archive, using link from the received message. Please double check the ‘spam’ or ‘junk’ folders if no e-mail received.
  12. Unzip the archive and burn the appeared firmware image to the known good micro SD card with ‘Win32DiskImager-0.9.5’ program.
  13. Insert micro SD card with the burned image into the device card reader and turn on the device by pressing ‘power on button’ for 1 sec.
  14. Following the instructions on display, make primary device settings.
  15. Power on the device and connect it via USB cable to your PC.
  16. Provide additional diagnostic procedures if needed (touch screen, Wi-Fi, etc.)
  17. Copy ‘Content’ folders to the root catalog of the internal microSD card of the device. Content is the same for all devices of this model and can be used constantly once downloaded. Link for downloading can be found in the e-mail message with firmware image archive download link. Please be noted, that mass-production content may differ from a customized (B2B) projects content.
  18. Reset device to factory defaults using internal Settings menu of the device.
